This paper deals with causal modeling and reasoning, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of structural equation models and simulation models suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a calculus of intervention, which is a concept that is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on axiomatization and formal reasoning suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.DS).
